libnoise
------------------------------------------
libnoise is a portable C++ library that is used to generate coherent noise, a
type of smoothly-changing noise. libnoise can generate Perlin noise, ridged
multifractal noise, and other types of coherent-noise.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.0.7-1
  libgcc1-7.4.0-1
  libnoise0-1.0.0-1bl1
  libstdc++6-7.4.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1
  ninja-1.9.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/qknight/libnoise

Canonical download:
  git://github.com/qknight/libnoise.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libnoise-1.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libnoise-1.0.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libnoise-1.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libnoise-1.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libnoise0-1.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libnoise-devel-1.0.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

